        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Bromley Kent</placeName>
                    <date>16 Wednesday | (after post-time)</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I sent the M.S. to M<hi rend="superscript">ess</hi>. Clowes on the 7<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> &amp; since then I have had only three sheets. I urged him to send me a sheet a day, stating the reason that my health is uncertain &amp; that I would not on any account suffer, what I did last time, when, being unwell, I had to look over three or four sheets the last day.— Now I see M<hi rend="superscript">s</hi>. Clowes is running the same course this time &amp; I write to inform you, that if the number sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> fail being ready it will be <hi rend="underline">exclusively the</hi> fault of M<hi rend="superscript">ess</hi>. Clowes for I cannot &amp; will not exert myself again, if I chance to be unwell</p>
<p>Will you be so kind as to take the affair in your own hands with M<hi rend="superscript">ess</hi>. Clowes.</p>
<p>My dear Sir | Yours very faithfully | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
    
        
